- Where's that club at?
- Just up a ways.

62
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,432
My God.

63
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:38,151
Tomorrow, World Geo and Accounting 201.

64
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,393
Yeah.

65
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:25,354
We agreed that you weren't gonna
make these kind of deals without
telling me about it first!

66
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:29,433
- I tried, but I had to act,
and I couldn't find you!
- And out of my account?

67
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,068
I don't like being told
that I can't write a check.

68
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:37,030
Selling short and all the rest of this
stock market crap makes no sense, Ricky.

69
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:40,636
You're betting on losing money; why don't
you just throw it away at the dog track?

70
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:44,395
I only made 4 Grand in 3 days!
What'd the store net last week?

71
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:47,074
This store has been very, very good to you.

72
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,515
If you spent half the time here
that you do on your deals,

73
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:52,478
- it could be even better.
- How many times do we
have to go through this?!

74
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:55,108
Yes, this store has been great to me.
No, I will not come in,

75
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,918
because there's no
future in retailing!

76
00:10:57,080 --> 00:11:00,277
- I don't see us hurting.
- Look, I want my own deals.

77
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,715
You know, one day, one of your
hunches is gonna backfire.

78
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:07,556
- I've gotta be able to trust you, Ricky.
- I'm not going anywhere, Mother!

79
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:11,678
And I'm sure as hell not gonna
bite the hand that so generously fed me.

