82
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,115
You and Rochelle get all those
T-shirts marked down?

83
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:00,995
Yes, Mrs. Chambers,
they're all priced on the shelf.

84
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,797
Well, next time, make more noise
when you come in.

85
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,556
I'm gonna be away for
a week starting Monday.

86
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,309
Ricky will be in to open up
and cover the upstairs.

87
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,270
There's one rule I have
for all my employees:

88
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:28,110
They don't date my son.
You understand that?

89
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,589
Yes'm.

90
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,674
It's so great being out of high school.

91
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,915
When I saw all the other kids
going back last month,

92
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,150
I felt like I was out of prison.

93
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:58,633
It's amazing how much you grow
in a couple of months.

94
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,796
Drive wild, Jimmy!

95
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,197
Jimmy's an artist.

96
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:28,475
Does airbrush. Shirts and stuff.

97
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,192
It's a glory to watch.

98
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:35,874
He's gonna teach me so that
I can do it next summer.

99
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:39,992
- Did you know Jimmy in school?
- I knew Ed.

100
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,958
It's his night to cook,
but I always help.

101
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:48,195
We all get along just fine, you know?

102
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,591
We're very liberated.

103
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,114
That's a neat old rocker.

104
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:02,675
Thanks.
It was my Granny's.

105
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:07,477
- You knew your Granny?
- Both of 'em. Grand-daddys, too.

106
00:14:09,699 --> 00:14:10,967
Wow.

107
00:14:11,803 --> 00:14:13,920
I barely knew my Ma.

108
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,913
<i>Where the hell you been?</i>

109
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,634
<i>- Did you run out of gas?
