harsh threats and the misery.

452
00:59:11,320 --> 00:59:14,517
You can't have that kind of comfort
without the hell threat coming somewhere.

453
00:59:16,200 --> 00:59:17,189
What?

454
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:18,713
<i>So clear and bright,</i>

455
00:59:18,920 --> 00:59:23,755
<i>like a crystal beacon lit
2000 years ago and still shining.</i>

456
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:26,793
<i>Obey and be saved in love.</i>

457
00:59:26,960 --> 00:59:31,112
<i>Turn away and be damned for all eternity.</i>

458
00:59:39,720 --> 00:59:42,109
My family bought it all.

459
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:44,911
Hook, line, and sinker.

460
00:59:46,360 --> 00:59:50,353
I grew up with the security and
certainty of living in the law.

461
00:59:52,960 --> 00:59:56,077
I also know the guilt
and shame it can bring.

462
00:59:59,520 --> 01:00:02,751
Nothing is ever gonna get
that kind of hold on me again.

463
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:09,232
My poor, tormented rebel from the law.

464
01:00:09,400 --> 01:00:11,436
I'm not your poor anything.

465
01:00:14,120 --> 01:00:16,350
I didn't mean any harm, Ruby.

466
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:19,239
Honest.

467
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:37,069
- Merry Christmas.
- Same to you.

468
01:00:37,280 --> 01:00:39,510
- Can you get the light?
- Yeah.

469
01:00:46,840 --> 01:00:49,513
<font color="#ffff00">Emily. Mike's Emily.</font>

470
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:52,078
<font color="#ffff00">Strange words.</font>

471
01:00:53,000 --> 01:00:55,434
<font color="#ffff00">Too many thoughts, but I
thumbed through the pages.</font>

472
01:00:57,560 --> 01:01:01,473
<font color="#ffff00">"To ache is human, not polite.</font>

473
01:01:02,600 --> 01:01:04,272
<font color="#ffff00">"The film upon the eye,</font>

474
01:01:05,960 --> 01:01:08,633
<font color="#ffff00">"Mortality's old custom,</font>

475
01:01:09,160 --> 01:01:11,196
<font color="#ffff00">"Just locking up</font>

476
