518
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:43,039
Get out of here, Ricky.

519
01:07:48,640 --> 01:07:50,119
Ruby...

520
01:07:52,600 --> 01:07:53,874
Ruby, Ruby, Ruby...

521
01:07:54,040 --> 01:07:57,919
A man offers you his heart,
and look at you.

522
01:08:06,960 --> 01:08:09,315
What's in this for you,
Miss Gissing?

523
01:08:18,880 --> 01:08:23,795
If you're not careful, you're gonna
end up one lonely, cock-teasing bitch!

524
01:08:26,440 --> 01:08:27,919
I should've known.

525
01:08:34,440 --> 01:08:35,589
I don't wanna see you around.

526
01:08:36,760 --> 01:08:40,196
In fact, don't even bother coming in
to work, 'cause you're fired. Terminated.

527
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:43,918
I'll send your last check here.

528
01:08:49,440 --> 01:08:50,839
I think it's for the best, don't you?

529
01:08:51,640 --> 01:08:55,599
I don't ever want to see you again.
I mean it.

530
01:09:43,800 --> 01:09:47,349
<font color="#ffff00">Driving along the road once,
I swerved trying not to hit a rabbit,</font>

531
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:50,150
<font color="#ffff00">and ran smack over a skunk.</font>

532
01:09:52,200 --> 01:09:54,395
<font color="#ffff00">I'm sorry, Ricky.</font>

533
01:09:55,400 --> 01:09:58,039
<font color="#ffff00">Guess nothing good can come
from being a fool.</font>

534
01:10:34,720 --> 01:10:38,918
<font color="#ffff00">Goddamn Ricky and his line about folks
being 2 paychecks from the streets.</font>

535
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:43,751
<i>Just make this right, here, and you'll
get back on that main road.</i>

536
01:10:43,920 --> 01:10:45,876
<font color="#ffff00">I met a family
from near back home.</font>

537
01:10:46,040 --> 01:10:47,917
<i>Either that, or you want to take this...</i>

538
01:10:48,080 --> 01:10:50,275
<font color="#ffff00">Everything they owned
was in their car.</font>

539
01:10:51,480 --> 01:10:54,631
<font color="#ffff00">Out of work and on their way to Mobile
to stay with a cousin.</font>

540
01:10:57,400 --> 01:11:00,039
<font color="#ffff00">I don't think the mom
was countin' on much.</font>

541
01:11:01,480 --> 01:11:03,391
<font color="#ffff00">I gave them $10 for gas.</font>

542
01:11:05,160 --> 01:11:08,277
<font color="#ffff00">Can't meet up with any more.
Not for a while, at least.</font>

543
01:11:10,760 --> 01:11:13,479
<font color="#ffff00">Not until I'm settled again
and unbeholden.</font>

544
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:10,512
- Hey.
- Hi.

545
01:12:13,080 --> 01:12:15,719
- How about a movie?
- I'm not feeling so good.

546
01:12:15,880 --> 01:12:17,791
I think I've got the flu.

547
01:12:18,600 --> 01:12:22,149
Really?  I'll come in and
make you some soup, then.

548
01:12:24,280 --> 01:12:25,918
I think I should just sleep.

549
01:12:32,360 --> 01:12:33,349
All right. You call me, alright?

550
01:12:34,160 --> 01:12:35,195
Yeah.

551
01:12:37,560 --> 01:12:39,596
Like a ghost,
I'm gonna haunt you.

552
01:13:28,760 --> 01:13:30,034
No.

553
01:13:31,120 --> 01:13:33,429
Well, I can do just about anything,
right there, I bet.

554
01:13:33,600 --> 01:13:36,160
- No, I don't know.
- Are you sure? 'Cause there
are plenty of people in here.

555
01:13:36,320 --> 01:13:40,313
I'm sure that you can add me right in,
and I can do something just fine for you!

556
01:14:44,760 --> 01:14:46,432
Good afternoon,
may I help you?

557
01:14:47,720 --> 01:14:48,948
No, um...

558
01:14:49,800 --> 01:14:52,268
I was supposed to meet someone.
I guess he's not here.

559
01:14:53,360 --> 01:14:54,634
No problem.

560
01:14:54,920 --> 01:14:57,036
Did you know you're not
supposed to be here alone?

561
01:14:59,480 --> 01:15:00,913
I sure didn't.

562
01:15:01,600 --> 01:15:02,874
We'll be seeing you around.

563
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:44,393
<font color="#ffff00">Impressive stuff.</font>

564
01:15:45,680 --> 01:15:48,253
<font color="#ffff00">To flaunt it in front of
paying customers.</font>

565
01:15:48,880 --> 01:15:50,996
<font color="#ffff00">The ultimate merchandise.</font>

566
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:56,589
<font color="#ffff00">Maybe that's all there is.
We're all selling.</font>

567
01:15:57,200 --> 01:16:00,829
<font color="#ffff00">Forget what's inside.
It's all in our skin...</font>

568
01:16:01,000 --> 01:16:03,958
<font color="#ffff00">and in what touches it,
what covers it, what hides it.</font>

569
01:16:05,200 --> 01:16:06,792
<font color="#ffff00">And what it can do.</font>

570
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:13,075
<font color="#ffff00">Too close to feeling gone.</font>

571
01:16:18,960 --> 01:16:20,916
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

572
01:16:24,440 --> 01:16:26,874
It was my problem,
I wanted to work it out myself.

573
01:16:28,040 --> 01:16:30,793
Didn't you just tell me Old Lady Chambers
said you were doing a great job?

574
01:16:32,360 --> 01:16:34,112
Why-- Why'd she fire you?

575
01:16:34,280 --> 01:16:37,636
There was no traffic in the store.
She had to.

576
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:41,156
Typical. Money's tight,
forget the worker, save your own ass.

577
01:16:41,600 --> 01:16:43,511
Not even a week's notice.

578
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:50,359
You'll get another job. And if you
need some money to see you through...

579
01:16:53,080 --> 01:16:56,595
- It's all right.
- Ruby, you could always move in here.

580
01:16:57,680 --> 01:17:02,151
Stay as long as you like.
I'll take real good care of you.

581
01:17:02,920 --> 01:17:04,319
It'd be wonderful.

582
01:17:09,000 --> 01:17:10,479
Every girl's dream.

583
01:17:14,520 --> 01:17:15,669
Right.

584
01:17:17,320 --> 01:17:18,799
Well, you think about it.

585
01:17:27,920 --> 01:17:30,070
For now, I'll just settle for
what you got in that pan.

586
01:17:35,680 --> 01:17:36,954
Saved it.

587
01:18:49,040 --> 01:18:50,678
Okay. Welcome.

588
01:18:56,920 --> 01:18:59,753
You take the top part of the sheet,
with the longest piece of hem...

589
01:18:59,920 --> 01:19:03,230
you put it all in one hand,
you draw it out

590
01:19:03,720 --> 01:19:06,029
and you set it in that basket.

591
01:20:24,080 --> 01:20:27,072
The first day is always
the toughest, but you'll make it.

592
01:20:27,360 --> 01:20:30,318
Though, none of us plan
to be here long, do we Wanda?

593
01:20:30,480 --> 01:20:33,870
But sometimes...
What you been doing?

594
01:20:35,720 --> 01:20:37,870
Sales. I've been in sales.

595
01:20:38,600 --> 01:20:40,192
Much better choice.

596
01:20:40,440 --> 01:20:43,876
The talkative one is Wanda.
I'm Persephina.

597
01:20:45,600 --> 01:20:46,749
Ruby.

598
01:20:47,840 --> 01:20:51,515
Well, Ruby, don't forget
to eat your Wheaties.

599
01:21:13,720 --> 01:21:17,269
Don't worry. Pretty soon,
you won't feel a thing.

600
01:21:48,760 --> 01:21:50,876
Why'd you wait
so long to tell me?

601
01:21:53,680 --> 01:21:56,558
Didn't I warn you about that man?
Didn't I warn you?

602
01:21:58,200 --> 01:22:00,191
Are you really mad or sad, Rochelle?

603
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:11,911
I could always join the Navy.

604
01:22:15,320 --> 01:22:18,392
Sure. Or marry a preacher
and have 15 babies.

605
01:22:18,680 --> 01:22:20,636
It's not your style, I'm afraid.

606
01:22:22,280 --> 01:22:25,670
- I've got 50, 60 dollars maybe...
- No...

607
01:22:26,160 --> 01:22:31,109
Yes. 50 would help.
Thanks.

608
01:22:32,120 --> 01:22:33,314
You'll get it back.

609
01:22:59,960 --> 01:23:02,838
<font color="#ffff00">On the edge of the edge,
a dream.</font>

610
01:23:04,840 --> 01:23:07,115
<font color="#ffff00">Everyone I'd ever known was there.</font>

611
01:23:08,280 --> 01:23:10,350
<font color="#ffff00">living on a beautiful mountain.</font>

612
01:23:15,120 --> 01:23:19,875
<font color="#ffff00">We all did our share.
We all felt joy in being alive.</font>

613
01:23:21,400 --> 01:23:26,394
<font color="#ffff00">Wild and free,
without harm, without sorrow.</font>

614
01:23:30,280 --> 01:23:32,032
<font color="#ffff00">Beyond reality.</font>

615
01:23:34,040 --> 01:23:35,837
<font color="#ffff00">Beyond fantasy.</font>

616
01:23:40,920 --> 01:23:42,353
<font color="#ffff00">Only there.</font>

617
01:23:45,720 --> 01:23:47,153
<font color="#ffff00">Only there.</font>

618
01:23:58,120 --> 01:23:59,394
Ruby ...

619
01:24:00,520 --> 01:24:01,714
Are you awake?

620
01:24:02,520 --> 01:24:04,238
Yeah, come on in.

621
01:24:21,240 --> 01:24:25,995
- You okay?
- Yeah, I've just been keeping
some late hours, is all.

622
01:24:28,320 --> 01:24:32,359
I brought you some chest pie.
It's the only thing my ma ever taught me.

623
01:24:34,560 --> 01:24:38,917
- <i>Debrah Ann! You coming back
today sometime?</i>
- Coming, Jimmy.

624
01:24:40,920 --> 01:24:42,797
I'll see you later.

625
01:25:10,440 --> 01:25:11,668
"What's that thing between Daddy's legs?"

626
01:25:11,840 --> 01:25:16,356
She says "Well, she's old enough to mind",
so she says, "That's how you get babies."

627
01:25:16,520 --> 01:25:19,796
"You put Daddy's thing together with
Mommy's thing, that's how you get babies.

628
01:25:19,960 --> 01:25:24,192
The girl, she's a little confused, she says:
"Mom, I was looking through the keyhole

629
01:25:24,360 --> 01:25:26,112
and I saw Daddy's thing
in your mouth."

630
01:25:26,280 --> 01:25:30,193
And she says
"Girl, that's how you get jewelry."

631
01:25:30,480 --> 01:25:31,959
I heard that.

632
01:25:52,280 --> 01:25:53,713
Looks like you're
getting the hang of it.

633
01:25:55,240 --> 01:25:57,834
- I don't think so.
- Well, that's good.

634
01:25:58,760 --> 01:26:00,034
Don't lose your mind.

635
01:26:33,240 --> 01:26:34,673
Hello, Ruby.

636
01:26:35,880 --> 01:26:37,313
Is it alright if I come in?

637
01:26:38,400 --> 01:26:39,719
Thank you.

638
01:26:40,600 --> 01:26:43,068
- Can I get you some tea?
- Oh, no thanks.

639
01:26:58,840 --> 01:26:59,909
I paid for that.

640
01:27:03,760 --> 01:27:05,637
I would never have
thought otherwise.

641
01:27:19,760 --> 01:27:23,196
Ricky told me that you came by the store
with the car loaded and left for home.

642
01:27:23,360 --> 01:27:25,351
Some emergency, he said.

643
01:27:28,160 --> 01:27:31,391
I was furious and hurt that
you hadn't even said goodbye.

644
01:27:32,120 --> 01:27:34,680
It wasn't until Rochelle called,
that I found out what really happened.

645
01:27:45,200 --> 01:27:49,318
My son is a lot like his
long-forgotten ass of a father.

646
01:27:52,200 --> 01:27:57,069
But I still have some hope for Ricky.
I know that must sound crazy.

647
01:28:00,080 --> 01:28:02,958
But you've got more pressing
concerns at the moment.

648
01:28:10,960 --> 01:28:12,473
I like mysteries.

649
01:28:13,480 --> 01:28:15,152
Ones with women detectives.

650
01:28:16,480 --> 01:28:18,152
I'd like to try one.

651
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:25,631
You know, when you first
came in the store,

652
01:28:26,240 --> 01:28:27,912
I didn't really need anybody.

653
01:28:29,520 --> 01:28:31,112
But I had a feeling about you.

654
01:28:36,200 --> 01:28:38,714
You reminded me of something,
you were hungry.

655
01:28:39,120 --> 01:28:40,872
There was a rage, and a...

656
01:28:41,040 --> 01:28:44,032
fury that I recognized
from a long time ago.

657
01:28:45,160 --> 01:28:46,912
A lot of good it's done me.

658
01:28:48,520 --> 01:28:50,317
Most of us learn to lay low.

659
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:52,992
Sounds like dying.

660
01:29:04,120 --> 01:29:06,156
Come on back
to the store, Ruby.

661
01:29:07,520 --> 01:29:11,832
You're doing fine, and I need
an Assistant Manager with
energy and good ideas.

662
01:29:12,520 --> 01:29:15,193
Besides, I'm thinking of opening
a second store, up the beach a ways.

663
01:29:16,160 --> 01:29:20,392
Lord knows, the way this
country's going, maybe nobody's
ever gonna buy anything again, but...

664
01:29:21,560 --> 01:29:24,393
Still, memories and dreams
are important.

665
01:29:25,960 --> 01:29:30,351
And, so are beach towels, swimsuits,
and suntan lotion. We gotta be ready.

666
01:29:32,000 --> 01:29:33,274
We'll have fun.

667
01:29:34,480 --> 01:29:37,040
And Ricky <i>will</i> leave you alone.

668
01:29:43,040 --> 01:29:44,871
All right, Mrs. Chambers.

669
01:29:46,720 --> 01:29:47,835
Mildred.

670
01:29:50,200 --> 01:29:52,668
- Mildred.
- Great.

671
01:29:54,600 --> 01:29:56,716
And now I think
I would like that tea.

672
01:30:08,040 --> 01:30:09,917
You going to wash in your dress clothes?

673
01:30:10,280 --> 01:30:11,349
No.

674
01:30:12,400 --> 01:30:14,868
I just came by to turn this in.
I got my old job back.

675
01:30:15,720 --> 01:30:17,790
Just when you were getting
the knack of it.

676
01:30:20,320 --> 01:30:23,073
Chambers Beach Emporium. Come by,
I'll give you a real good deal.

677
01:30:28,960 --> 01:30:30,552
<i>- Wanda?
- Yeah.</i>

678
01:30:31,960 --> 01:30:33,757
<font color="#ffff00">I dream about that room.</font>

679
01:30:35,320 --> 01:30:38,835
<font color="#ffff00">And Wanda, and Persephina.</font>

680
01:30:42,520 --> 01:30:45,557
<font color="#ffff00">Am I up to remembering that
we're all in the same world?</font>

681
01:30:46,520 --> 01:30:48,875
<font color="#ffff00">I don't know. I hope so.</font>

682
01:30:51,520 --> 01:30:53,317
<font color="#ffff00">I know it won't be easy.</font>

683
01:31:02,240 --> 01:31:05,550
Well, keep it up, girls. After this,
we're gonna tackle the upstairs.

684
01:31:05,720 --> 01:31:09,269
At this rate, it's gonna take us
10 years to get the store restocked.

685
01:31:35,400 --> 01:31:37,231
Y'all got enough stuff now?

686
01:31:38,440 --> 01:31:42,149
I'll get the door for you.
Y'all come back now, y'hear?

687
01:31:42,400 --> 01:31:44,755
Thanks a lot.
Tell your friends about us.

688
01:31:47,600 --> 01:31:49,875
Thank God for spring.

689
01:31:54,217 --> 01:31:57,039
And the "Best Buns on the Beach"
contest continues!

690
01:31:57,320 --> 01:32:01,233
Ladies in the house, can you make some noise for contestant number 6, Jeff.

691
01:32:01,400 --> 01:32:05,916
Is that you? Go do your duty, man. Ladies,
make some noise! Get this guy movin' for ya.

692
01:32:07,720 --> 01:32:09,915
Wiggle it.
Not just a little bit.

693
01:32:11,160 --> 01:32:13,833
Ladies, are you at Party Spring Break?
Make some noise!

694
01:32:34,600 --> 01:32:37,273
Where's the party at?
Give it up!

695
01:32:38,920 --> 01:32:42,959
Let's rock the house!
Shock the house!

696
01:32:46,880 --> 01:32:50,793
It's Spring Break, y'all, time to
cut loose, on Panama City Beach.

697
01:32:54,560 --> 01:32:58,030
How many people need sex on the beach
while you're here this weekend?

698
01:32:59,680 --> 01:33:01,033
Safe sex, safe sex.

699
01:33:01,200 --> 01:33:04,715
I'm gonna send out two girls right here
with some more t-shirts, guys.

700
01:33:05,840 --> 01:33:10,277
Safe Spring Break party.
Don't drive while you're drunk.

701
01:33:10,440 --> 01:33:12,829
Put your sunscreen on
and be sure...

702
01:33:13,000 --> 01:33:15,753
to be safe with sex
on Panama City Beach.

703
01:33:16,120 --> 01:33:20,159
The 3 big S's of Spring Break. Who needs
a t-shirt? My ladies have'em for ya.

704
01:33:21,160 --> 01:33:23,594
You gotta make some noise, guys!
Where they goin'?

705
01:33:25,960 --> 01:33:28,520
Spring Break capital of the
United States, Panama City Beach.

706
01:33:28,680 --> 01:33:31,194
If you guys are feeling good,
make some noise!

707
01:33:51,560 --> 01:33:55,792
- Not the most gorgeous shade of blue.
- Yeah, but one size fits all.

708
01:33:56,640 --> 01:33:58,312
You got the other side?

709
01:33:58,880 --> 01:34:00,598
- Okay.
- Let's go to work.

710
01:34:00,760 --> 01:34:03,877
These knobs set your price, look through
the little window and make sure it's right.

711
01:34:04,120 --> 01:34:05,314
Give it a good, hard squeeze,

712
01:34:05,480 --> 01:34:07,835
and then just roll it..  on like that.

713
01:34:08,000 --> 01:34:10,355
On someplace flat. Alright?
You wanna try?

714
01:34:15,800 --> 01:34:17,950
Ruby...
Never mind.

715
01:34:18,360 --> 01:34:20,237
- Rochelle ...
- Yes, Mrs. Chambers?

716
01:34:20,400 --> 01:34:23,551
- Has the new stock been priced yet?
- The new girls are putting it on the floor.

717
01:34:23,720 --> 01:34:25,153
Great, thank you.

718
01:34:48,240 --> 01:34:50,834
It's nothing like when I first started.

719
01:34:51,000 --> 01:34:52,998
You wouldn't believe the
inventory that we're moving.

720
01:34:53,000 --> 01:34:55,791
We get all this stuff,
and the next day, it's gone.

721
01:34:55,960 --> 01:34:59,111
Mildred says it's a buying frenzy.
Like it's contagious, or something.

722
01:35:01,680 --> 01:35:03,272
What do you think about all this,
Rochelle?

723
01:35:03,480 --> 01:35:07,234
It's what we're gettin' paid for, isn't it?
When the fish bite, enjoy.

724
01:35:10,440 --> 01:35:13,432
- Like lemmings to the sea.
- What?

725
01:35:17,040 --> 01:35:18,234
Nothing.

726
01:35:21,360 --> 01:35:22,952
Beats not working.

727
01:35:26,080 --> 01:35:27,479
There were other options.

728
01:35:30,360 --> 01:35:31,509
What do you mean?

729
01:35:58,720 --> 01:36:02,110
No matter how much they mess things up,
there's always the ocean.

730
01:36:02,680 --> 01:36:03,954
Yeah.

731
01:36:04,120 --> 01:36:07,829
Polluted and dying.
There it is.

732
01:36:12,040 --> 01:36:16,556
I'm glad you finally called me. I was
beginning to think I was a leper or something.

733
01:36:18,080 --> 01:36:20,878
I got caught up in gettin'
the store ready for spring.

734
01:36:23,120 --> 01:36:26,749
It can't mean anything,
going back to the selling game.

735
01:36:26,920 --> 01:36:29,912
It doesn't mean anything
It can't be the reason you're here.

736
01:36:34,040 --> 01:36:36,600
It's a game whose rules I understand.

737
01:36:41,160 --> 01:36:44,118
And for a while, at least, that's
just gonna have to be enough.

738
01:36:46,960 --> 01:36:49,235
What are you really
trying to say, anyway?

739
01:36:51,080 --> 01:36:53,036
It's better than
having no game at all.

740
01:37:08,200 --> 01:37:11,112
You and all of your
gloom and doom crap, man.

741
01:37:11,600 --> 01:37:13,591
Do something about it
or leave it alone.

742
01:37:15,320 --> 01:37:18,915
Just please stop looking down
at the rest of us.

743
01:37:28,280 --> 01:37:29,713
You're absolutely right.

744
01:37:32,840 --> 01:37:34,239
I'm sorry.

745
01:37:38,760 --> 01:37:40,193
Me too.

746
01:38:05,920 --> 01:38:08,275
<font color="#ffff00">That's when I started
seeing less of Mike.</font>

747
01:38:13,600 --> 01:38:15,477
<font color="#ffff00">We go to movies and stuff,</font>

748
01:38:15,840 --> 01:38:19,116
<font color="#ffff00">but we get uncomfortable if
we stay together for too long.</font>

749
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:24,550
<font color="#ffff00">He's working on something.
One of his causes again.</font>

750
01:38:25,960 --> 01:38:27,393
<font color="#ffff00">But he won't say what.</font>

751
01:38:28,720 --> 01:38:30,392
<font color="#ffff00">May be afraid of losing it.</font>

752
01:38:32,040 --> 01:38:33,439
<font color="#ffff00">I understand.</font>

753
01:38:35,280 --> 01:38:37,111
<font color="#ffff00">I hope we keep in touch.</font>

754
01:38:43,640 --> 01:38:47,110
<font color="#ffff00">Somewhere I heard that "Hell is
when all your dreams come true.</font>

755
01:38:50,320 --> 01:38:53,710
<font color="#ffff00">Maybe it's because you find out,
they won't all go together.</font>

756
01:38:54,840 --> 01:38:58,958
<font color="#ffff00">Or that there's always sides you
can't see when you're dreaming away.</font>

757
01:39:03,240 --> 01:39:04,798
I won't be staying long.

758
01:39:05,200 --> 01:39:08,670
I just wanted to tell you
how much I regret what happened.

759
01:39:12,520 --> 01:39:14,272
I'm in counseling now.

760
01:39:15,320 --> 01:39:17,436
"Getting in touch with myself,"
they call it.

761
01:39:18,200 --> 01:39:19,394
Becoming a new man.

762
01:39:25,200 --> 01:39:29,716
I just wanted to apologize,
that's all.

763
01:39:35,400 --> 01:39:36,913
Maybe I'll see you around?

764
01:39:45,360 --> 01:39:46,952
Business is booming.

765
01:40:43,840 --> 01:40:45,717
While we have a free moment...

766
01:40:48,720 --> 01:40:51,553
Thanks, Rochelle.
It was a real help.

767
01:40:51,720 --> 01:40:55,110
Oh, yeah.
I'd forgotten. Almost.

768
01:40:57,840 --> 01:41:00,195
By rights, Mildred should
have made you Assistant.

769
01:41:02,640 --> 01:41:06,792
Nah, after this summer, Mildred
won't be able to afford this one here.

770
01:41:07,560 --> 01:41:11,189
Billy finishes school in December.
And I'll have my degree, and...

771
01:41:11,360 --> 01:41:12,998
we'll be straight.

772
01:41:14,240 --> 01:41:15,514
I hope.

773
01:43:02,360 --> 01:43:03,793
Hello.

774
01:43:04,720 --> 01:43:05,869
Hello.

775
01:43:06,400 --> 01:43:09,836
- Did you used to work over at Porter's Court?
- Oh, my uncle's place.

776
01:43:10,400 --> 01:43:11,594
I still do.

777
01:43:11,760 --> 01:43:15,594
He and my father just bought this complex,
and we're fixing it up.

778
01:43:16,080 --> 01:43:19,834
- Do you live here?
- Yeah, I do.

779
01:43:20,920 --> 01:43:24,117
- Would you like to have some tea?
- Sure.

780
01:43:37,720 --> 01:43:39,358
What about that song?

781
01:43:40,560 --> 01:43:43,438
Prayers to Shiva,
who is everything.

782
01:43:44,080 --> 01:43:45,513
Everything?

783
01:43:47,040 --> 01:43:50,430
When my family came here,
we were skin and bones.

784
01:43:50,960 --> 01:43:53,315
I mean it, we were skin and bones.

785
01:43:54,000 --> 01:43:58,198
But four years later, and look at me now.
I'm so healthy, don't you think?

786
01:43:59,400 --> 01:44:02,437
- Don't you miss your home?
- This is home now.

787
01:44:02,600 --> 01:44:07,469
- Everyone wants to be here.
- It doesn't make it right.

788
01:44:09,160 --> 01:44:11,833
It is, for now,
the great dream of the world.

789
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:15,515
Whether it's right or wrong,
that's always much harder.

790
01:44:22,360 --> 01:44:24,191
It really is a beautiful song.

791
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:26,558
Maybe you'd like to learn it?

792
01:44:32,920 --> 01:44:34,831
- <i>Good morning, Mr. Roberts.</i>
- <i>Mornin'.</i>

793
01:44:49,640 --> 01:44:51,790
<font color="#ffff00">Suppose it means more.</font>

794
01:44:52,440 --> 01:44:55,591
<font color="#ffff00">Making it in some
big great city somewhere.</font>

795
01:44:58,400 --> 01:45:00,595
<font color="#ffff00">But this is the world I found.</font>

796
01:45:03,640 --> 01:45:06,393
<font color="#ffff00">And I guess the questions
stay the same.</font>

797
01:45:06,840 --> 01:45:08,558
Mornin', Ruby.

798
01:45:15,960 --> 01:45:18,155
<font color="#ffff00">Like, where does caring come from?</font>

799
01:45:23,560 --> 01:45:26,472
<font color="#ffff00">Can we ever know our true desires?</font>

800
01:45:33,080 --> 01:45:37,358
<font color="#ffff00">And why are we, all of us,
so often lonely and afraid?</font>

801
01:45:41,840 --> 01:45:45,515
<font color="#ffff00">The answers are probably
real simple and real close.</font>

802
01:45:47,440 --> 01:45:50,716
<font color="#ffff00">Smiling somewhere, quiet-like.</font>

803
01:45:53,320 --> 01:45:55,151
<font color="#ffff00">Waiting, for us.</font>

804
01:46:18,800 --> 01:46:20,518
Mornin', everybody.

